That's fine. As I said, AI isn't for all fields. It obviously is going to fail at ones where text prediction and the likes just doesn't work. Many fields can utilize AI though as either a productivity tool or a business tool. Intent Analysis is pretty crazy when it comes to handling support tickets-

or any other forms of communication. You can identify hostile people before they reach your staff. By either rejecting tickets or something, you can actually help better the job quality of your staff. That's a win in my book. It can also be used for public discourse to try to stem hate and violence.

AI itself is a tool to be used where it makes sense. It's not meant to be shoved into everything (which unfortunately everyone's doing but that's how it goes with new techs until we understand what it can't handle).
